16 shall mean within six months of the acquisition. Such disclosure shall include, at a
17 minimum:
18 (1) A description of the asset or interest acquired;
19 (2) The date of acquisition;
20 (3) The consideration given for such acquisition;
21 (4) The identification of any assets pledged by the electric membership corporation to
22 secure a loan or other funding that forms all or a portion of the consideration pledged to
23 secure such loan or other funding;
24 (5) The total amount of the electric membership corporation's assets, debts, and
25 obligations and those of its gas subsidiaries;
26 (6) The total amount of the electric membership corporation's electric generation and
27 transmission assets as defined by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Uniform
28 System of Accounts; and
29 (7) The percentage of the electric membership corporation's net utility plant used for the
30 purposes described in subsection (b) of Code Section 46-4-164.
31 (b) An electric membership corporation shall disclose to its members the annual cost of
32 gas in aggregate that it sells. Such disclosure shall be made on an annual basis."
33 SECTION 2.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
